    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.1-2_0001"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline><add>Nov 2</add></dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I really enjoyed talking to you again. Circumstances have made it impossible for me to spend time with you as I would like to. When I am with you it is like touching history and it is unfortunate that the opportunity has not been available for me to return to Missouri for a while.</p> 
                
                <p>I made an attem<del/><add>p</add>t to obtain Mrs Aly's thesis but could not as the att<del/>ached letter will explain. I would appreciate it if you could facilitate matters. Also let me know the exact name and author of the <hi rend="caps">M.A.</hi> thes<del>e</del><add>i</add>s written about you as it was not clear over the phone.</p>
                
                <p>You know how detailed Mr's Aly's thes<del>e</del><add>i</add>s is and whether it covers pertinent present day information about yourself such as your family and your farm. If it doesn't could you fill me in on that data.</p>
                
                <p>I have written a synopsis of "Three Friends" because I want to mail it to many independents and I only have one copy of the poem. Besides a synopsis can be made to emphasize the more salient salable feat<del>y</del><add>u</add>res. As soon as it is edited and the final draft is ready, I will send it to you. I would like it if you would put in letter form permission for me to represent you as far as this work is concerned so that in case there are any questions by any studio <del/><add>i</add>nterested I can prove my position. There is no need for any contract between us because our relationship is not one of that nature. I would like to know though, the minimum you would accept for the screen rights so I could deal accordingly. I still have high hopes and some day the two of us will be watching "The Story of Three Friends" filmed. My wife sends regards as she already considers you a dear friend. Take good care of yourself</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely</salute>
                    <signed>Bob Leaf</signed>
                </closer>
                    
            </div1>
            
